exercise:



Let \mathbb Z be the set of integers,
\mathbb E=\left\{x\in\mathbb Z\middle|x\text{ is even}\right\},
\mathbb D=\mathbb Z\setminus\mathbb E,
\mathcal P(X)=\left\{Y\middle|Y\subseteq X\right\} for any set X,
[X]^1=\left\{Y\subseteq X\big||Y|=1\right\} for any set X, and
[X]^2=\left\{Y\subseteq X\big||Y|=2\right\} for any set X.



Determine which of the symbols \in,\subseteq (if either)
can be used to relate each of the following items with the sets
\mathbb Z,\mathbb E,\mathbb D,
the sets
\mathcal P(\mathbb Z),\mathcal P(\mathbb D),\mathcal P(\mathbb E),
the sets
[\mathbb Z]^1,[\mathbb E]^1,[\mathbb D]^1, and
the sets
[\mathbb Z]^2,[\mathbb E]^2, and [\mathbb D]^2.
Give an explanation for each valid relationship.


